	(2194,515,'_activities_1_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(2195,515,'activities_1_activity_description','We think it will be useful for all the delegates to go through a briefing about how the broadcast machine works, what they require from guests on the program, and how to manage the physical demands as well as an idea of what good looks like from a radio and TV perspective.\r\n\r\nWe will run through the newsroom drivers and how the individuals need to manage them, in conjunction with their advisers. The topics that we will cover are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  to produce a good story that gets on the show. For delegates, knowing what actually makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  We will introduce the three participants to the Bladonmore preparation process and give them time to work on some messages with support. We will then spend the rest of the session testing and refining these messages in various radio and TV interviews.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
