	(2469,546,'conclusions','At the beginning of the session, we asked you about your personal brand and how you wanted to come across, you said:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>Knowledgeable </em></strong> yes, you were able to give clear insight to the way a court room works and why it is important to both defendant and alleged victim that the accused has legal representation.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>Approachable </em></strong> yes, from the start, you ensured that you said good morning to the BBC Radio 5 Live listeners, despite a tricky opening question from Nicky Campbell</li>\r\n 	<li><strong><em>Respected - </em></strong>Yes, you constantly convey concern that there should be a chance of justice for all sides in a particularly sensitive area.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe key point is to build-in a preparation process in partnership with Myddleton ahead of all media engagements that allows you to identify your key messages and develop memorable proof points to support them. You have the style and gravitas to be an excellent media asset for BCL Solicitors.\r\n\r\nIf there is anything more Bladonmore can help with, please do not hesitate to get in contact with us through Paul, Deborah or Paula.\r\n\r\nKind regards,\r\nMatt Guarente and Susan Bookbinder\r\n\r\n&nbsp;'),
