	(1920,485,'activities_3_activity_name','Theory: Understanding the media - The clash of agendas'),
	(1921,485,'_activities_3_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(1922,485,'activities_3_activity_description','At this point we will turn our attention to media handling skills.\r\n\r\nWe will begin by delivering a short presentation that provides a framework for understanding how the media works. The topics we will cover are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom </strong> What pressures does a journalist face, what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist  </strong>Journalists want a good story, but what exactly makes a good story? We provide a framework for understanding how journalists judge information and the criteria they apply before deciding to publish an article.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Creating your own agenda </strong> This is the crux of our approach. We will give Mr. Catella a preparation process so that he goes into interviews with the ammunition he needs to perform well.'),
