	(2796,559,'conclusions','Well done Hugues on a real baptism of fire! Its not easy doing training then having to do an interview with a tier one newspaper, but youdid so successfully.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>I look forward to seeing you in Paris next week to continue your development.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>Kind regards,<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\nBen Shore and Matthew Guarente'),
	(2794,559,'more_work','<b>Front-load your ideas</b> journalists are hard-wired to accept the big idea followed by the evidential support for the idea. This is not a natural way to organiseinformation,but it works in media engagement.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span><b>Evidential</b><b>support</b>- Evidenceis usually what is quoted because it helps readers understand your top-line messaging:<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"13\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"1\" data-aria-level=\"1\">the 50bn data events you see daily<span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233279&quot;:true}\"></span></li>\r\n 	<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"13\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"2\" data-aria-level=\"1\">the unique positioning oftelcosto have a more holistic view of cyber-defence<span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233279&quot;:true}\"></span></li>\r\n 	<li data-leveltext=\"\" data-font=\"Symbol\" data-listid=\"13\" aria-setsize=\"-1\" data-aria-posinset=\"3\" data-aria-level=\"1\">the very good analogy that security isnt a fortress<span data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;134233279&quot;:true}\"></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Bridging</b>: thinking about how you can get from the question you are asked, to the things you want to say. This requires an alert mindset in which you identify a route from one topic to another.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<b><i>Set boundaries</i></b>. You shouldnt accept an unreasonable question, nor an unreasonable amount of questions, for example on Huawei. Establish your line: stick toit andkeep sticking to it.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span><span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\nYoushouldmanage your speed of speech more effectively.<b><i></i></b><b><i>Its</i></b><b><i>OK to stop and think before responding</i></b>. Your brain often presents several ideas that you COULD choose to respond with; if you give it a little time, you are able to choose what you SHOULD say. The gap is normally about two seconds.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>'),
	(2793,559,'_went_well','field_5b21350c1cb97'),
	(2791,559,'_overview','field_5b1023299fc62'),
	(2792,559,'went_well','<ul>\r\n 	<li style=\"text-align: left;\">In a very compressedtimescale,you did an excellentjob of assimilatingour suggestionsand deployingthemin the interview with Stephen Wilmot.</li>\r\n 	<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span><b><i>In your second interview, you used what we call signposting to impose a structure on the conversation</i></b>. There are two parts to this or I think the answer is a little complex gives the listener (the journalist) a very brief instruction about what they are about to hear.<b><i>This technique also made your responses longer</i></b>. There are many benefits to this, not least of which is that you will have to face fewer questions.</li>\r\n 	<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>In our practices<b><i>, you started to use the bigger picture as a way of getting away from specific issues</i></b>. In the second interviewfor example, you were much more proactive in getting away from the details ofSecureDataand onto the bigger strategy piece  well done.</li>\r\n 	<li><span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>In the interview with Stephen<b><i>you stopped the conversation and backtracked on your messaging about the competitive advantage that</i></b><b><i>telcos</i></b><b><i>have in overseeing the network</i></b>. Well done! Interviewees sometimes feel that they are breaking a rule that forbids them from breaking the flow of the interview  but it isbeterto dothat thannot deliver your narrative.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
	(2790,559,'overview','DearHugues,<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>It was good to meet youat our media coaching sessionyesterday.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>In the note belowwecapture the main feedback points from the session, where you performed well, and wherethere are areas for improvement.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>You can also look back at your performances in the secure online video gallery. The link and password are here:<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span><span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<b><i>Introduction</i></b>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>In the session,wetalked through OCDscore messaging, both in relation to theSecuredatatransaction andwider issues such as the cybersecurity market and Huawei.<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>\r\n\r\n<span data-ccp-props=\"{}\"></span>We then simulatedtwo interviews from the perspective of the Heard on The Street Column of theWall Street Journal'),
