	(2993,575,'activities_0_activity_name','Introductions and objective setting; Intro from Myddleton Communications'),
	(2994,575,'_activities_0_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(2995,575,'activities_0_activity_description','The Bladonmore team will introduce themselves to and set some context for the session. Then the Myddleton team will make some comments about the nature of the work that we do and that the purpose of the coaching is to arm Harry, Richard, Guy and Shaul with the techniques and confidence to take advantage of media opportunities that will enable them to promote their own practices and the firms brand and also to take on active competitors in their market.'),
	(2996,575,'_activities_0_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(2997,575,'activities_0_activity_start','13:00:00'),
	(2998,575,'_activities_0_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(2999,575,'activities_0_activity_end','13:15:00'),
	(3000,575,'_activities_0_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3001,575,'activities_1_activity_name','Understanding the media: the clash of agendas'),
	(3002,575,'_activities_1_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3003,575,'activities_1_activity_description','We think it will be useful for all the delegates to go through a briefing about how the broadcast machine works, what they require from guests on the program, and how to manage the physical demands as well as an idea of what good looks like from a radio and TV perspective.\r\n\r\nWe will run through the newsroom drivers and how the individuals need to manage them, in conjunction with their advisers. The topics that we will cover are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  to produce a good story that gets on the show. For delegates, knowing what actually makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  We will introduce the four participants to the Bladonmore preparation process and give them time to work on some messages with support. We will then spend the rest of the session testing and refining these messages in various radio and TV interviews.'),
	(3004,575,'_activities_1_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3005,575,'activities_1_activity_start','13:15:00'),
	(3006,575,'_activities_1_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3007,575,'activities_1_activity_end','13:45:00'),
	(3008,575,'_activities_1_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3009,575,'activities_2_activity_name','Interview 1: Today Programme for Harry and Richard; BBC Radio Five Live for Shaul and Guy'),
	(3010,575,'_activities_2_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3011,575,'activities_2_activity_description','We will craft a setting for each of the participants to respond to some questions.\r\n\r\nHarry and Richard will answer questions from Dom OConnell on the Today Programme, whilst Shaul and Guy will face BBC Radio Five Live. Each will be about a broader issue and perhaps also focusing into their own work. They will each have time to prepare using support from Myddleton Communications as required.'),
