	(3559,601,'activities_0_activity_name','Introductions and objective setting; Intro from Myddleton Communications'),
	(3560,601,'_activities_0_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3561,601,'activities_0_activity_description','The Bladonmore team will introduce themselves and set some context for the session. We will welcome the Myddleton team to comment about the nature of the work that we do and that the purpose of the coaching is to arm the participants with the techniques and confidence to take advantage of media opportunities that will enable them to promote their own practices and the firms brand, and also to take on active competitors in their market.'),
	(3562,601,'_activities_0_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3563,601,'activities_0_activity_start','13:00:00'),
	(3564,601,'_activities_0_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3565,601,'activities_0_activity_end','13:10:00'),
	(3566,601,'_activities_0_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3567,601,'activities_1_activity_name','Understanding the media: the clash of agendas'),
	(3568,601,'_activities_1_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3569,601,'activities_1_activity_description','We discussed in the briefing call that although John, Julian and Ellen have seen a short version of this presentation for the broadcast media, we believe that it will be helpful for them to see a more detailed illustration of how the <u>print</u> media operates and the pressures on journalists to get their stories published.\r\n\r\nWe will run through the newsroom drivers and how the individuals need to manage them, in conjunction with their advisers. The topics that we will cover are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  to produce a good story that gets on the show. For delegates, knowing what actually makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  We will introduce the participants to the Bladonmore preparation process and give them time to work on some messages with support. We will then spend the rest of the session testing and refining these messages in various exercises.'),
	(3570,601,'_activities_1_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3571,601,'activities_1_activity_start','13:10:00'),
	(3572,601,'_activities_1_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3573,601,'activities_1_activity_end','13:40:00'),
	(3574,601,'_activities_1_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3575,601,'activities_2_activity_name','Exercise 1: National Newspaper Interviews - The Financial Times/The Guardian'),
	(3576,601,'_activities_2_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3577,601,'activities_2_activity_description','We will ask the delegates to divide into two groups as follows:\r\n\r\nGroup 1: John, Jane, Shula and Richard\r\n\r\nGroup 2: Ellen, Julian, Rachel and Paul\r\n\r\nWe will explain that we are dividing them up so that they can gain the maximum benefit of the training; working together on four separate exercises and deciding each time who should represent the group, so every delegate will take part in at least one exercise.\r\n\r\nWe will remind the delegates that however specialist a journalist maybe, they will not possess their level of expertise and still need to speak in the language of the audience, which may be at a higher level of awareness than, for example, The Sun, but they are not practising lawyers at the top of their game. We will ask each group to brief a spokesperson for either of the above publications.'),
	(3578,601,'_activities_2_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3579,601,'activities_2_activity_start','13:40:00'),
	(3580,601,'_activities_2_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3581,601,'activities_2_activity_end','14:40:00'),
	(3582,601,'_activities_2_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3583,601,'activities_3_activity_name','Exercise 2:  Building Relationships: Briefing a new journalist at Law 360  the effect of Brexit on the law and European Arrest Warrant'),
	(3584,601,'_activities_3_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3585,601,'activities_3_activity_description','The Bladonmore coaches and Myddleton team will explain the value of helping a journalist to get stories published. Its also important to gain their trust so that BCL Solicitors becomes a go-to source for background and ultimately comment, leading to comments in the nationals and articles in the trade press and raising awareness in the trade press.\r\n\r\nWe will give the groups time to work on a briefing and deliver it. We will film and review the two briefing sessions.'),
	(3586,601,'_activities_3_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3587,601,'activities_3_activity_start','14:40:00'),
	(3588,601,'_activities_3_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3589,601,'activities_3_activity_end','15:30:00'),
	(3590,601,'_activities_3_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3591,601,'activities_4_activity_name','Exercise 3: Pitching a story and gaining an interview with Regional Press'),
	(3592,601,'_activities_4_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3593,601,'activities_4_activity_description','We will again ask delegates to split into groups and decide on two different spokespersons to initially pitch the story to the newsdesk and another to speak to a regional paper that they have strategically targeted. We will have explained the importance of offering local detail to a regional journalist, therefore this exercise is aimed at enabling the delegates to get BCL Solicitors into the regional headlines by offering journalists a story which will help their careers and build valuable relations with the firm.\r\n\r\nWe will suggest stories such as the surge in county lines networks  which gangs use to transport drugs out of cities to rural areas and which has been blamed for the increase in child drug offences across the country (West Mercia has seen a 42% y-o-y increase in drug offences committed by children aged between 10 and 17), or a fraud case in Manchester that involves local doctors. We will give the delegates time to develop a story and pitch it to a regional editor. We will film and review the exercise.'),
	(3594,601,'_activities_4_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3595,601,'activities_4_activity_start','15:30:00'),
	(3596,601,'_activities_4_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3597,601,'activities_4_activity_end','16:15:00'),
	(3598,601,'_activities_4_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3599,601,'activities_5_activity_name','Exercise 4: Press Conferences'),
	(3600,601,'_activities_5_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3601,601,'activities_5_activity_description','We will ask the groups to decide on a chair and a subject matter. We suggest that BCL Solicitors advice on the growing concerns regarding privacy and cybersecurity threats. We will conduct two short press conferences and ask each group to become press reporters and fire questions at the other and then swap over.\r\n\r\nThis will give delegates the chance to work together and consolidate all the learning points, regarding giving regional angles to local press reporters and using the vocabulary that will work for each publication. It also gives us the opportunity to advise delegates on the importance of performance - even in a press setting - as well as content and presenting as a united front when representing BCL Solicitors on a public platform.'),
