	(3737,603,'activities_4_activity_description','We will again ask delegates to split into groups and decide on two different spokespersons to initially pitch the story to the newsdesk and another to speak to a regional paper that they have strategically targeted. We will have explained the importance of offering local detail to a regional journalist, therefore this exercise is aimed at enabling the delegates to get BCL Solicitors into the regional headlines by offering journalists a story which will help their careers and build valuable relations with the firm.\r\n\r\nWe will suggest stories such as the surge in county lines networks  which gangs use to transport drugs out of cities to rural areas and which has been blamed for the increase in child drug offences across the country (West Mercia has seen a 42% y-o-y increase in drug offences committed by children aged between 10 and 17), or a fraud case in Manchester that involves local doctors. We will give the delegates time to develop a story and pitch it to a regional editor. We will film and review the exercise.'),
	(3738,603,'_activities_4_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3739,603,'activities_4_activity_start','15:30:00'),
	(3740,603,'_activities_4_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3741,603,'activities_4_activity_end','16:15:00'),
	(3742,603,'_activities_4_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3743,603,'activities_5_activity_name','Exercise 4: Press Conferences'),
	(3744,603,'_activities_5_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3745,603,'activities_5_activity_description','We will ask the groups to decide on a chair and a subject matter. We suggest that BCL Solicitors advice on the growing concerns regarding privacy and cybersecurity threats. We will conduct two short press conferences and ask each group to become press reporters and fire questions at the other and then swap over.\r\n\r\nThis will give delegates the chance to work together and consolidate all the learning points, regarding giving regional angles to local press reporters and using the vocabulary that will work for each publication. It also gives us the opportunity to advise delegates on the importance of performance - even in a press setting - as well as content and presenting as a united front when representing BCL Solicitors on a public platform.'),
