	(3781,604,'activities_0_activity_end','13:10:00'),
	(3782,604,'_activities_0_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(3783,604,'activities_1_activity_name','Understanding the media: the clash of agendas'),
	(3784,604,'_activities_1_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(3785,604,'activities_1_activity_description','We discussed in the briefing call that although John, Julian and Ellen have seen a short version of this presentation for the broadcast media, we believe that it will be helpful for them to see a more detailed illustration of how the <u>print</u> media operates and the pressures on journalists to get their stories published.\r\n\r\nWe will run through the newsroom drivers and how the individuals need to manage them, in conjunction with their advisers. The topics that we will cover are:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  to produce a good story that gets on the show. For delegates, knowing what actually makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  We will introduce the participants to the Bladonmore preparation process and give them time to work on some messages with support. We will then spend the rest of the session testing and refining these messages in various exercises.'),
	(3786,604,'_activities_1_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(3787,604,'activities_1_activity_start','13:10:00'),
	(3788,604,'_activities_1_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(3789,604,'activities_1_activity_end','13:40:00'),
