	(4381,619,'activities_1_activity_name','Media theory '),
	(4382,619,'_activities_1_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(4383,619,'activities_1_activity_description','Inthenext phase we will deliver our media theory segment entitled The Clash of agendas. This presentation looks at the different outcomes that interviewers and interviewees want from press engagement and considers some strategies for how both parties can get something useful from the interaction.The presentation breaks down into three modules:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Power in the newsroom What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li>The agenda of a journalist How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda to write a good story- knowing what makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n 	<li>Creating your own agenda This is the crux of our approach. We will giveHuguesa preparation process so thathegoesin to interviews with the ammunitionheneedsto perform well.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
