	(5293,659,'activities_2_activity_name','Media Theory: the clash of agendas'),
	(5294,659,'_activities_2_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(5295,659,'activities_2_activity_description','This presentation looks at the different outcomes that interviewers and interviewees want from press engagement and considers some strategies for how both parties can get something useful from the interaction.\r\n\r\nThe presentation breaks down into three modules:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  <em>to write a good story</em> - knowing what makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  This is the crux of our approach. We will give the group a preparation process so that the participants go in to interviews with the ammunition they need to perform well.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
	(5296,659,'_activities_2_activity_description','field_5b11098d14d46'),
	(5297,659,'activities_2_activity_start','14:15:00'),
	(5298,659,'_activities_2_activity_start','field_5b11105bbe3d5'),
	(5299,659,'activities_2_activity_end','14:35:00'),
	(5300,659,'_activities_2_activity_end','field_5b111097bf5d2'),
	(5301,659,'activities_3_activity_name','Simulated interviews'),
	(5302,659,'_activities_3_activity_name','field_5b11097814d45'),
	(5303,659,'activities_3_activity_description','In the next phase we will do a series of two interviews with selected participants, on the stage. Each interview will be from a different perspective, the first with TechCrunch, the second with the BBC. The idea is to give the group a sense of (a) the kinds of questions they could encounter and (b) the different requirements of a range of journalists  clearly network TV is materially different to a phone interview with TechCrunch. Each interview will be videoed and the footage played back for constructive review.'),
