	(5872,719,'activities_2_activity_description','This presentation looks at the different outcomes that interviewers and interviewees want from press engagement and considers some strategies for how both parties can get something useful from the interaction.\r\n\r\nThe presentation breaks down into three modules:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Power in the newsroom</strong>  What pressures does a journalist face and what are their prime motivators?</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>The agenda of a journalist</strong>  How do those pressures manifest themselves? The journalist has an agenda  <em>to write a good story</em> - knowing what makes a good story can help manage the interview.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Creating your own agenda</strong>  This is the crux of our approach. We will give the group a preparation process so that the participants go in to interviews with the ammunition they need to perform well.</li>\r\n</ul>'),
